                  | Working as a software engineer with Stack Moxie, I quickly proved myself to be capable of managing large-scale projects independently. In my time with the company, I shipped three entirely new, full-stack features on which I handled all aspects of development. In my development work, I combine a commitment to strong technical foundations, a focus on excellent user experience, and a passion for clean design to craft features that have scaled to serve all Stack Moxie's clients, from small startups to enterprise-grade giants. 
                p
                  | In addition to the native features I developed for Stack Moxie, I also developed integrations with partners including Salesforce, Amplitude, and others. To achieve seamless integrations, I worked hand-in-hand with outside development teams at other companies, utilizing my communication skills to provide the projects with direction and effectively convey technical requirements to outside teams. The integrations I developed brought partners' features into the Stack Moxie ecosystem and integrated Stack Moxie's testing functionalities into other applications. 
                p
                  | I also assisted in managing the cloud infrastructure on which Stack Moxie runs. I handled several aspects of our migration from AWS to Azure including creating the CI/CD process, configuring deployment pipelines, migrating to Azure Service Bus, and preparing to migrate fully onto an Azure-hosted regime instead of Heroku in the future. 
                p
                  | Prior to becoming an engineer, I attained my law degree from Washington University in St. Louis and worked as a legal consultant for firms and startups specifically on issues around data privacy, including GDPR and CCPA, corporate formation, and regulatory and compliance issues. I maintain an active California Bar license. 
